{{Infobox website | name = JamesEdition.com | logo = [[File:James Edition logo.png|300px]] | logo_size = | logo_alt =JamesEdition.com | logo_caption = JamesEdition Logo | screenshot = | collapsible = <!-- set as "on", "y", etc, otherwise omit/leave blank --> | collapsetext = <!-- collapsible area's heading (default "Screenshot"); omit/leave blank if collapsible not set --> | background = <!-- for collapsetext heading; default grey (gainsboro) --> | screenshot_size = <!-- default 300px --> | screenshot_alt = | caption = | url = {{URL|www.jamesedition.com}} | commercial = Yes | registration = | language = English | num_users = | content_license = <!-- or: | content_licence = --> | owner = JamesEdition B.V.<ref>http://www.jamesedition.com/about</ref> | author = <!-- or: creator / authors / creators --> | editor = <!-- or: | editors = --> | launch_date = {{start date and age|2008}} (as JamesList) | company_type = Private company | type = Classifieds, luxury, media | foundation = {{start date and age|2008}} (as JamesList) | location_city = [[Amsterdam]] | location_country = Netherlands<ref>{{cite web | access-date=June 29, 2016 | url=http://www.jamesedition.com/about/contact | title= JamesEdition - Home/About/Contact}}</ref> | revenue = | alexa = {{WikidataAlexa}} | ip = | current_status = Active | website = {{official URL}} | predecessor = JamesList | programming language = Ruby on Rails | key people = {{ubl|Noam Perski (CEO JamesList 2009-2011)|Roman Bach (CEO)}} }}
'''JamesEdition''' ('''JE''') is a global online luxury marketplace with headquarters in Amsterdam, Netherlands. The website has 15 different categories. These are: [[real estate]], [[cars]], [[jewellery]], [[jet aeroplane|jets]], [[helicopters]], [[watches]], [[yachts]], extraordinaire, [[motorcycles]], lifestyle & collectibles, residential developments, experiences, yachts and vacation rentals.
Sellers can post their offers to JamesEdition and will be published after editorial review. It is an elite form of a [[Classified advertising]] portal. The strict curation of all listings have resulted in several media coverages. Some listings have been posted to [[Top Gear (2002 TV series)|Top Gear]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.topgear.com/uk/car-news/one-off-lamborghini-sogna-for-sale-2013-12-11 |title=Buy the weirdest Lambo concept ever - BBC Top Gear |publisher=Topgear.com |date=2013-12-11 |accessdate=2014-02-28}}</ref> and [[Guardian.co.uk|The Guardian]]<ref>{{cite web|author=Ben Beaumont-Thomas |url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2014/feb/28/batman-batmobile-tumbler-on-sale |title=Street-legal Batmobile goes on sale for $1m – and even has a CD player &#124; Film |publisher=theguardian.com |date= |accessdate=2014-02-28}}</ref> websites. It has been referred to by some as [[Craigslist]] for the rich<ref>{{cite news | first=Sapna | last=Maheshwari | title=There's A Secret Craigslist Just For Rich People | date=July 20, 2014 | publisher= | url = https://www.buzzfeed.com/sapna/theres-a-little-known-craigslist-just-for-rich-people | work =Buzzfeed }}</ref> or even "Craigslist for billionaires".<ref>{{cite web | first=Derek | last=Sall | title=9 Top Luxury Purchases From JamesEdition – The Craigslist for Billionaires | date=March 5, 2015 | url = http://personalprofitability.com/luxury-purchases-jamesedition-the-craigslist-for-billionaires/}}</ref> The advertised goods are so rare that the website has received regular coverage by other websites, print magazines and TV stations.<ref>{{cite news | first=Emmie | last=Martin | title=The super wealthy have their own exclusive versions of Amazon, Tinder and Instagram | date=May 10, 2017 | publisher= | url = https://finance.yahoo.com/news/super-wealthy-own-exclusive-versions-142927457.html | work =CNBC }}</ref>
==History== The company was founded 2008. It changed its name from JamesList to JamesEdition in February 2013, after becoming the defendant in a lawsuit by [[Craigslist]] in June 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://domainnamewire.com/2012/07/20/craigslist-sues-jameslist/|title=CraigsList sues JamesList, the "Craigslist for the rich"|accessdate=28 February 2014|date=20 July 2012|author=Andrew Allemann|website=Domain Name Wire}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.aimgroup.com/2013/03/05/craigslist-gets-its-way-well-almost-with-jameslist/|title= Craigslist gets its way (well, almost) with Jameslist |accessdate=13 February 2017|date=5 March 2013|author=Lars Herlin|website=AIM Group}}</ref> In 2016 the company changed its shareholders structure, appointed a new CEO<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.aimgroup.com/2016/08/11/jamesedition-to-restart-with-new-ceo/|title=JamesEdition to restart with new CEO |accessdate=13 February 2017|date=11 August 2016|author=Lars Herlin|website=AIM Group}}</ref> and moved the company from Sweden to the Netherlands.<ref>https://www.jamesedition.com/about/contact</ref> In 2017 it was reported that JamesEdition would expand its business model beyond classifieds.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://balkanbusinesswire.com/stories/511079439-classified-executives-to-gather-in-belgrade-for-spring-conference|title=Classified executives to gather in Belgrade for spring conference|accessdate=13 February 2017|date=5 February 2017|author=John Breslin|website=Balkan Business Wire}}</ref>
